dataIdInfo.idAbs: The Find Subnetworkstool accepts a USGS NHD stream network as a shapefile, finds all disconnected networks within the dataset. Optionally the tool can find topological errors within the network, and will label associated features with an error code.

tool.name: FindSubnetworksTool

param.name: InputStreamNetwork
param.dialogReference: Line shapefile representing a stream network. We recommend using a USGS NHD flowline dataset. All canal features (i.e. FCode = 336) must be removed priot running the tool.

param.name: OutputStreamNetwork
param.dialogReference: Line shapefile produced by the tool. This shapefile will include new attributes, including a unique identifier code for each subnetwork stored in the '_netid_' attribute field.

param.name: BoolError
param.dialogReference: Indicates if the tool will find and label potential topological erros within each subnetwork.

tool.summary: The Find Subnetworkstool accepts a USGS NHD stream network as a shapefile, finds all disconnected networks within the dataset. Optionally the tool can find topological errors within the network, and will label associated features with an error code.
